[recto] Horace SHIPP, The Original 'Winter Landscape with Bird Trap' by Pieter Bruegel in the Collection of M.A. Hassid, Esq., Apollo, London, LIX, January 1954, p. 1 [...]; [verso] [toegevoegde vermelding]: Where did Friedländer say that? I can only find that in his article 'Zur Londoner Leihausstellung belgischer Kunst', Der Cicerone XIX, 1927, [citaat] p. 216 [...]. Horace SHIPP, The Flemish Masters, London [Newnes], 1953, Plate XII The Bird Trap (in black and white). In list of plates, p. 10 Plate XII. The Bird Trap Pieter Bruegel the Elder. Panel 16 x 22 1/2 inches. Signed and dated 1564. In the coll. of M.A. Hassid, Esq. (Another version painted following year is in a private collection in Brussels).
